1
00:00:00,300 --> 00:00:01,460
[Disclaimer:
All depicted events are fictional

2
00:00:01,500 --> 00:00:02,660
and for entertainment purposes only;
viewer discretion is advised]

3
00:00:14,640 --> 00:00:18,560
[Love Upon a Time Series]

4
00:00:19,400 --> 00:00:20,460
My Lord,

5
00:00:20,860 --> 00:00:22,080
the fault is mine alone.

6
00:00:22,410 --> 00:00:23,790
I can wait no longer.

7
00:00:24,660 --> 00:00:25,450
Uncle.

8
00:00:26,280 --> 00:00:29,920
Can you escort me to my manor?

9
00:00:44,380 --> 00:00:46,260
How did we

10
00:00:46,490 --> 00:00:47,720
get to know each other?

11
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:51,280
I wasn't here to have fun?

12
00:00:51,880 --> 00:00:53,000
No, Master.

13
00:00:54,760 --> 00:00:56,440
You have simply held me in your fond regard.

14
00:01:02,950 --> 00:01:04,440
I can't concentrate at all.

15
00:01:04,970 --> 00:01:07,010
Why is he constantly on my mind?

16
00:01:26,270 --> 00:01:28,740
Uncle, I can't handle a boat very well.

17
00:01:28,780 --> 00:01:30,420
Can you escort me to my manor?

18
00:02:16,090 --> 00:02:17,090
Phop,

19
00:02:18,440 --> 00:02:19,570
I'm sorry.

20
00:02:24,660 --> 00:02:26,360
I am relieved to know you are safe.

21
00:02:29,130 --> 00:02:30,320
Pray, come inside.

22
00:02:38,890 --> 00:02:39,800
Phop.

23
00:02:44,570 --> 00:02:45,490
Phop!

24
00:03:46,510 --> 00:03:47,730
Even if he's mad,

25
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:50,030
he still acts nice, doesn't he?

26
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:56,620
If he insulted me like before,
I wouldn't feel this guilty.

27
00:03:59,420 --> 00:04:00,740
How terrifying.

28
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:03,760
If my feelings for him grow even more,

29
00:04:04,130 --> 00:04:05,740
what's going to happen?

30
00:04:09,500 --> 00:04:11,370
[Love Upon a Time Series]

31
00:05:21,120 --> 00:05:24,760
[Love Upon a Time Series]

32
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:30,880
Master Klao!

33
00:05:31,190 --> 00:05:32,200
Master Klao!!

34
00:05:32,580 --> 00:05:33,320
Master Klao.

35
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:35,960
Master, you have not yet fully recovered.
Pray, take some rest.

36
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:39,800
Kong, move.

37
00:05:40,550 --> 00:05:41,800
I want to talk to Phop.

38
00:05:42,280 --> 00:05:43,690
Lord Phop... He...

39
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:45,040
He is away on patrol, Master.

40
00:05:45,490 --> 00:05:47,920
If so, then who are you waiting here for?

41
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:52,000
I am merely here to rest a while.

42
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:54,640
The breeze is most agreeable here.

43
00:06:07,540 --> 00:06:09,160
Lord Phop has requested that
you not visit him.

44
00:06:09,260 --> 00:06:11,920
He is gravely ill,
having been out in the rain all night.

45
00:06:12,340 --> 00:06:15,120
He fears you may also be taken ill by him.

46
00:06:30,950 --> 00:06:34,000
My Master Klao, my little angel.

47
00:06:34,310 --> 00:06:36,150
Pray, take a few bites for my sake.

48
00:06:36,190 --> 00:06:38,520
These are all your favorites.

49
00:06:41,970 --> 00:06:44,760
I have kept all chilies
from the kitchen today,

50
00:06:44,940 --> 00:06:47,930
so that the dishes
are not in the least spicy.

51
00:06:54,940 --> 00:06:58,600
If you desire something else, pray tell me.

52
00:06:58,750 --> 00:07:01,220
Deer, mouse-deer, Eld's deer,

53
00:07:01,260 --> 00:07:03,320
elephants, turtles,
lice, fleas, or seashells?

54
00:07:03,520 --> 00:07:05,120
Say but the word,

55
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:07,950
and I shall go and hunt it for you.

56
00:07:07,980 --> 00:07:09,640
Oh, Muan,

57
00:07:09,730 --> 00:07:12,510
no soul takes pleasure in lice and fleas.

58
00:07:12,760 --> 00:07:15,320
Good heavens.
Even Lord Phop has eaten termites, Sai.

59
00:07:55,120 --> 00:07:55,900
Master Klao.

60
00:07:58,180 --> 00:07:59,140
Chuay!

61
00:08:15,140 --> 00:08:17,480
And I was foolishly glad

62
00:08:17,860 --> 00:08:20,800
to see Master Klao
smiling and laughing once more.

63
00:08:20,950 --> 00:08:23,280
I had thought things
would return to the way they were.

64
00:08:24,410 --> 00:08:26,660
What is your meaning in saying so?

65
00:08:26,700 --> 00:08:28,680
When Master Klao returned from Phichit,

66
00:08:29,090 --> 00:08:30,690
he seemed...

67
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:32,320
In those days,

68
00:08:32,780 --> 00:08:34,679
he was in such high spirits.

69
00:08:36,159 --> 00:08:38,440
Whenever he visited,

70
00:08:38,530 --> 00:08:40,840
he would bring books for discussion.

71
00:08:41,330 --> 00:08:46,480
Even the most complex and difficult matters,
the two would discuss together,

72
00:08:47,150 --> 00:08:49,420
as though they alone
in the world understood.

73
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:52,320
Aunt...

74
00:08:56,170 --> 00:08:58,790
He was well when he returned from Phichit,

75
00:08:59,140 --> 00:09:04,370
but within a few months,
they fell to quarreling morning and night.

76
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:09,120
At times, they would grow sullen
and refuse to speak to one another.

77
00:09:11,860 --> 00:09:14,950
So you brought liquor into the manor,
though I forbade you to go to the tavern?

78
00:09:15,040 --> 00:09:17,010
Do not give me cause to worry so, Klao!

79
00:09:17,520 --> 00:09:18,820
I am truly weary of this!!

80
00:09:25,160 --> 00:09:27,760
Then cease your worrying over me.

81
00:09:28,520 --> 00:09:30,540
I shall not remain here
to trouble you any longer!

82
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:32,280
Chuay!

83
00:09:33,650 --> 00:09:35,640
Go and gather my belongings,

84
00:09:35,780 --> 00:09:37,880
and move everything to the small manor.

85
00:09:39,670 --> 00:09:42,480
Once the High Lord
returns from his official duties,

86
00:09:43,730 --> 00:09:45,520
I shall inform him of this matter.

87
00:09:49,460 --> 00:09:50,480
Chuay!

88
00:09:51,460 --> 00:09:53,180
What are you dawdling for?

89
00:09:53,540 --> 00:09:54,420
Now!

90
00:10:03,060 --> 00:10:05,360
Since then, Master Klao
has not returned to the main manor.

91
00:10:05,640 --> 00:10:08,500
Rather than being so dedicated to
his studies for the examination,

92
00:10:08,710 --> 00:10:10,480
he began going out
and idling away his time.

93
00:10:12,500 --> 00:10:17,470
At first, I understood that
he was grieving for his father

94
00:10:17,530 --> 00:10:19,840
and needed some distraction.

95
00:10:21,230 --> 00:10:25,400
But as time passed, it seemed
he had truly fallen into a life of heavy drinking.

96
00:10:25,850 --> 00:10:29,280
At that time,
Lord Phop was much distressed on his account.

97
00:10:29,660 --> 00:10:31,370
Whenever Master Klao went out,

98
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:33,400
Lord Phop would neither eat

99
00:10:33,720 --> 00:10:35,220
nor sleep in peace.

100
00:10:35,750 --> 00:10:37,920
He would often secretly wait
at the small manor,

101
00:10:38,230 --> 00:10:41,040
exposed to the elements
until he fell gravely ill.

102
00:10:43,920 --> 00:10:45,280
Worst of all,

103
00:10:45,590 --> 00:10:49,120
they were still estranged
and not on speaking terms

104
00:10:49,450 --> 00:10:50,840
until the very day

105
00:10:51,930 --> 00:10:53,320
Master Klao disappeared.

106
00:10:57,610 --> 00:10:59,500
At times, I cannot help but feel that

107
00:10:59,810 --> 00:11:02,960
his madness might actually be a blessing.

108
00:11:03,210 --> 00:11:05,440
For all his strange and erratic speech,

109
00:11:05,700 --> 00:11:08,960
it is better that he has been able to forget
the tragedies of the past.

110
00:11:09,080 --> 00:11:13,450
Mm. The most heartwarming sight
was Master Klao and Lord Phop,

111
00:11:13,510 --> 00:11:16,360
laughing and chatting as in days past.

112
00:11:16,970 --> 00:11:20,160
But I never thought they would
come to quarrel like this all over again.

113
00:11:20,380 --> 00:11:21,880
It is true.

114
00:11:31,540 --> 00:11:33,300
I am so afraid,

115
00:11:33,670 --> 00:11:36,920
for I fear they shall never speak to
each other again.

116
00:11:37,410 --> 00:11:38,920
Or worst of all,

117
00:11:39,380 --> 00:11:42,620
I fear Master Klao might vanish once more.

118
00:11:45,010 --> 00:11:48,360
Once before, I nearly lost
all that I held dear.

119
00:11:49,750 --> 00:11:52,100
I know too well the agony it brings.

120
00:11:53,950 --> 00:11:56,200
I wish for such sorrow
never to strike again,

121
00:11:58,140 --> 00:11:59,960
neither upon myself

122
00:12:01,330 --> 00:12:02,960
nor upon my friend.

123
00:12:35,730 --> 00:12:37,280
What is the matter, Jom?

124
00:12:38,070 --> 00:12:39,550
Why have you grown so quiet?

125
00:12:40,260 --> 00:12:41,200
Nothing.

126
00:12:41,830 --> 00:12:43,400
But with you staring at me thus,

127
00:12:44,330 --> 00:12:45,800
it is ruining my appetite.

128
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:55,610
The other day,
you scolded me before everyone,

129
00:12:57,230 --> 00:12:59,160
and now you treat me with such coldness.

130
00:13:00,550 --> 00:13:03,680
I prepared your favorite meal,
hoping we might move past this,

131
00:13:10,560 --> 00:13:12,200
but I regret ever coming here.

132
00:13:21,480 --> 00:13:22,960
Sit down, will you?

133
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:24,890
I have not yet said a word.

134
00:13:53,050 --> 00:13:55,040
I truly do not understand you.

135
00:13:56,780 --> 00:13:59,040
Is it so difficult
to speak kindly to me for once?

136
00:14:01,320 --> 00:14:02,480
In the past,

137
00:14:02,780 --> 00:14:04,600
you used to protect me.

138
00:14:05,420 --> 00:14:06,800
So why...

139
00:14:08,130 --> 00:14:11,320
now that we have grown older, must you speak
such cruel words that break my heart?

140
00:14:19,290 --> 00:14:21,260
Would you care for some cloth?

141
00:14:22,390 --> 00:14:24,720
- May I interest you in my fine cloth?
- Yes.

142
00:14:31,710 --> 00:14:32,880
Might I offer you a cloth?

143
00:14:33,550 --> 00:14:35,870
What a dainty
and lovely little piece of cloth.

144
00:14:35,900 --> 00:14:39,000
The Farangi use it to wipe away sweat,

145
00:14:39,100 --> 00:14:40,420
and it is much favored indeed.

146
00:14:40,820 --> 00:14:41,920
Would you like one?

147
00:14:45,240 --> 00:14:46,400
This one

148
00:14:47,320 --> 00:14:49,040
should suit a man like you best.

149
00:14:51,420 --> 00:14:55,040
I prefer soft and light shades
such as this one.

150
00:14:56,880 --> 00:14:57,740
I see.

151
00:15:06,990 --> 00:15:08,280
His name is Kaew,

152
00:15:08,860 --> 00:15:11,440
the youngest son of High Lord Sintaranurak.

153
00:15:11,820 --> 00:15:13,690
His household has only sons.

154
00:15:13,840 --> 00:15:17,640
Kaew was an unexpected addition,
born long after the others.

155
00:15:18,260 --> 00:15:19,620
Word has it that

156
00:15:19,980 --> 00:15:22,360
his mother raised her sons like daughters,

157
00:15:22,510 --> 00:15:24,320
keeping them at home
to do housework all day.

158
00:15:25,210 --> 00:15:27,520
What a strange household they are.

159
00:15:27,970 --> 00:15:29,600
Raising sons as though
they were daughters…

160
00:15:30,020 --> 00:15:31,280
Have they no sense of shame?

161
00:15:31,310 --> 00:15:32,200
Mm...

162
00:15:32,440 --> 00:15:35,280
To have effeminate sons,
who would not feel ashamed?

163
00:15:49,040 --> 00:15:50,520
Kaew is a good man

164
00:15:50,740 --> 00:15:51,890
who conducts himself well.

165
00:15:52,170 --> 00:15:55,160
Being close to his mother,
his nature is quite understandable.

166
00:15:55,980 --> 00:15:57,110
Jom.

167
00:15:57,350 --> 00:15:59,080
And you should better know this:

168
00:15:59,380 --> 00:16:02,720
High Lord Sintaranurak
has a kinsman within the palace walls,

169
00:16:04,070 --> 00:16:06,070
a eunuch preacher,

170
00:16:06,340 --> 00:16:07,960
who has risen far higher in rank than you.

171
00:16:12,640 --> 00:16:13,960
Jom, let us leave.

172
00:16:16,690 --> 00:16:18,160
Whenever someone scolded me,

173
00:16:19,050 --> 00:16:20,960
you were always the first to defend me.

174
00:16:23,530 --> 00:16:26,820
So why must you be the one
to hurt me like this?

175
00:16:34,910 --> 00:16:36,220
Look at how you protect one another.

176
00:16:36,620 --> 00:16:38,920
One might think you are husband and wife.

177
00:16:38,990 --> 00:16:40,480
Or is it merely a little fling?

178
00:17:03,020 --> 00:17:03,900
Well...

179
00:17:06,230 --> 00:17:08,040
I scold only you, and no one else.

180
00:17:10,530 --> 00:17:11,800
But why?

181
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:16,240
I only see you as a younger brother.

182
00:17:19,540 --> 00:17:20,960
But why?

183
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:28,960
Because...

184
00:17:32,220 --> 00:17:34,320
- we have been friends since childhood and...
- Not true.

185
00:17:37,380 --> 00:17:39,840
You do not scold Klao as you do me.

186
00:17:40,660 --> 00:17:42,200
He, too, is our childhood friend.

187
00:17:43,860 --> 00:17:44,940
Jom.

188
00:17:46,260 --> 00:17:48,390
At times you push me away,

189
00:17:49,530 --> 00:17:51,520
yet at times you are so kind to me.

190
00:17:54,400 --> 00:17:56,440
How do you truly feel about me?

191
00:18:12,250 --> 00:18:13,680
I treasure you.

192
00:18:16,080 --> 00:18:17,860
You are my only companion.

193
00:18:19,270 --> 00:18:20,600
You bring me water

194
00:18:21,780 --> 00:18:22,800
and food

195
00:18:24,560 --> 00:18:26,360
and assist me in every way.

196
00:18:29,350 --> 00:18:31,640
I must be strict with you at times,

197
00:18:32,140 --> 00:18:34,200
but only to prepare you for this world,

198
00:18:35,640 --> 00:18:37,160
so that you may support yourself

199
00:18:41,170 --> 00:18:44,520
and remain safe
from the malice and gossip of others.

200
00:18:46,670 --> 00:18:47,880
Jom...

201
00:18:49,510 --> 00:18:51,120
I, too,

202
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:54,920
have only you as my companion.

203
00:19:57,900 --> 00:19:58,900
Physician!

204
00:19:59,530 --> 00:20:01,240
Are you here at present?

205
00:20:05,850 --> 00:20:08,080
Leave. I have patients to attend to.

206
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:11,040
- But Jom...
- Leave at once.

207
00:20:13,040 --> 00:20:15,500
Just a moment! I am coming down!

208
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:20,040
I see you only as a younger brother.

209
00:20:20,670 --> 00:20:22,220
Do not ever do such a thing again.

210
00:21:31,820 --> 00:21:33,160
Wrong time...

211
00:21:33,720 --> 00:21:35,510
Wrong circumstances.

212
00:21:36,860 --> 00:21:38,880
Restore what was lost
and set wrongs aright.

213
00:21:41,980 --> 00:21:42,980
No.

214
00:21:43,880 --> 00:21:45,120
My father is innocent.

215
00:21:47,740 --> 00:21:48,740
Good heavens.

216
00:21:50,240 --> 00:21:51,360
Master Klao.

217
00:21:59,200 --> 00:22:00,200
My Lord?

218
00:22:00,480 --> 00:22:01,750
Are you quite well now?

219
00:22:03,510 --> 00:22:04,800
Quiet.

220
00:22:26,060 --> 00:22:27,560
Has he been in this state for long?

221
00:22:32,310 --> 00:22:33,670
Earlier today,

222
00:22:33,940 --> 00:22:35,160
he was quite well, my Lord.

223
00:22:37,660 --> 00:22:38,560
But...

224
00:22:40,630 --> 00:22:41,700
What is it?

225
00:22:47,900 --> 00:22:49,200
Master Klao

226
00:22:49,690 --> 00:22:52,200
rose at dawn to see you.

227
00:22:54,060 --> 00:22:57,080
He had been out in the scorching sun,
watching over you all day

228
00:22:57,560 --> 00:22:58,880
without food, my Lord.

229
00:22:59,490 --> 00:23:02,620
By evening, he began to lapse
into delirium, as you see.

230
00:23:19,640 --> 00:23:21,160
He is very hot to the touch.

231
00:23:25,540 --> 00:23:27,080
Go and fetch a damp cloth.

232
00:23:27,670 --> 00:23:29,240
Tell the servants in the kitchen

233
00:23:29,470 --> 00:23:31,880
to prepare a batch of herbal fever medicine.

234
00:23:35,120 --> 00:23:36,050
Go now.

235
00:23:36,800 --> 00:23:37,600
Yes, my Lord.

236
00:23:56,040 --> 00:23:57,160
Forgive me.

237
00:23:59,020 --> 00:24:01,880
I promise I shall never again
treat you with such distance or anger.

238
00:25:07,600 --> 00:25:08,660
Home...

239
00:25:10,750 --> 00:25:11,920
I want to go home.

240
00:25:34,080 --> 00:25:35,490
Fear not,

241
00:25:41,320 --> 00:25:43,360
for I shall be your home.

242
00:26:50,450 --> 00:26:51,450
Two rounds

243
00:26:52,210 --> 00:26:53,440
of the lash.

244
00:26:55,130 --> 00:26:56,250
Father!

245
00:26:57,920 --> 00:26:59,090
Father!!

246
00:26:59,120 --> 00:26:59,920
Klao!

247
00:27:06,020 --> 00:27:07,200
Cease this!

248
00:27:08,340 --> 00:27:09,760
My father is guiltless!

249
00:27:11,440 --> 00:27:13,000
Restrain yourself, my brother,

250
00:27:13,460 --> 00:27:14,960
lest you too shall face legal punishment.

251
00:27:17,350 --> 00:27:19,030
He is guiltless!

252
00:27:19,530 --> 00:27:22,760
If you seek his life, take mine instead!!

253
00:27:26,810 --> 00:27:28,410
Have some consideration for your father.

254
00:27:29,210 --> 00:27:30,940
How would he feel were he to hear this?

255
00:27:36,260 --> 00:27:38,400
My father commits no foul deeds.

256
00:27:41,920 --> 00:27:43,600
He bears ill will toward no one.

257
00:27:45,760 --> 00:27:48,080
My father is being wrongly accused!

258
00:27:51,750 --> 00:27:52,920
Dear Klao.

259
00:27:53,740 --> 00:27:56,000
Act with prudence.

260
00:28:04,640 --> 00:28:06,880
Prudence be damned!

261
00:28:08,260 --> 00:28:10,080
I care only

262
00:28:11,020 --> 00:28:12,760
to find

263
00:28:13,300 --> 00:28:14,920
every soul

264
00:28:15,240 --> 00:28:17,320
who bore false witness against my father!

265
00:28:18,100 --> 00:28:20,160
And they shall meet their end

266
00:28:20,520 --> 00:28:22,550
by my hand!

267
00:28:22,890 --> 00:28:24,720
- Unhand me!
- Klao!

268
00:28:29,540 --> 00:28:30,840
Stay away from me!

269
00:28:34,940 --> 00:28:36,320
Get a hold of yourself, Klao.

270
00:28:36,370 --> 00:28:37,840
Should Cherd dare to slander your father,

271
00:28:38,000 --> 00:28:39,760
do you think His Excellency
would believe him,

272
00:28:39,910 --> 00:28:41,040
being but a commoner?

273
00:28:41,170 --> 00:28:43,190
Confronting him
would only court greater danger.

274
00:28:44,410 --> 00:28:45,640
I care not!

275
00:28:45,800 --> 00:28:48,840
I must hunt down whosoever
bore false witness against my father!

276
00:28:58,280 --> 00:28:59,280
Hey!

277
00:29:03,830 --> 00:29:07,240
So you brought liquor into the manor,
though I forbade you to go to the tavern?

278
00:29:09,490 --> 00:29:11,660
Do not give me cause to worry so, Klao!

279
00:29:11,960 --> 00:29:13,480
I am truly weary of this!!

280
00:29:55,360 --> 00:29:56,670
Klao suspected Cherd,

281
00:29:57,640 --> 00:29:59,030
so he confronted him.

282
00:29:59,680 --> 00:30:00,880
It wasn't just about Pim.

283
00:30:01,510 --> 00:30:04,160
I don't know whether
he framed Lord Preechapiban,

284
00:30:04,430 --> 00:30:06,760
but it is possible that
he was the one who killed Klao.

285
00:30:08,620 --> 00:30:09,620
Klao?

286
00:30:12,590 --> 00:30:14,680
He thought Klao was dead.

287
00:30:15,210 --> 00:30:18,140
Klao should've died,
as the fortune teller said.

288
00:30:18,650 --> 00:30:20,800
However, I was placed in Klao's place,

289
00:30:20,980 --> 00:30:23,380
which is why Cherd looked so shocked,
as if he had seen a ghost.

290
00:30:26,320 --> 00:30:27,590
Cherd is a troublemaker.

291
00:30:27,860 --> 00:30:30,230
Even if Phop doesn't know
whether Klao is dead or alive,

292
00:30:30,430 --> 00:30:32,110
it's understandable
that he would be worried.

293
00:30:35,740 --> 00:30:36,740
Phop

294
00:30:37,470 --> 00:30:39,280
has loved you all this time, Klao.

295
00:30:44,260 --> 00:30:45,040
Master Klao.

296
00:30:46,330 --> 00:30:47,440
Has your condition improved?

297
00:30:49,520 --> 00:30:50,360
Mm.

298
00:30:53,160 --> 00:30:55,100
You must've stayed by my side all night.

299
00:30:55,980 --> 00:30:57,640
Thank you, Chuay.

300
00:30:59,060 --> 00:31:00,850
Why did you thank me, Master?

301
00:31:01,170 --> 00:31:03,280
It is Lord Phop
you should be thanking instead.

302
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:49,480
Did I wake you up?

303
00:31:51,380 --> 00:31:53,020
I have been awake for some time.

304
00:31:53,960 --> 00:31:55,380
I simply have not regained my strength yet.

305
00:32:05,860 --> 00:32:07,210
You're still burning up.

306
00:32:07,860 --> 00:32:09,230
Do take the herbal medicine.

307
00:32:30,280 --> 00:32:31,720
I can manage on my own.

308
00:32:34,270 --> 00:32:36,280
You're still sick.
Don't try to act so tough.

309
00:32:37,020 --> 00:32:38,720
You've been taking care of me a whole lot.

310
00:32:38,980 --> 00:32:40,360
Let me return the favor.

311
00:32:51,120 --> 00:32:52,080
Bitter...

312
00:32:55,470 --> 00:32:56,720
I thought so.

313
00:32:57,550 --> 00:32:59,800
Muan prepared me for this.

314
00:33:33,940 --> 00:33:36,360
It gets rid of the bitterness
and your fussiness.

315
00:34:14,650 --> 00:34:15,679
I...

316
00:34:16,620 --> 00:34:18,219
I'm sorry

317
00:34:19,130 --> 00:34:20,130
for...

318
00:34:20,949 --> 00:34:23,060
making you worry about me all the time.

319
00:34:25,070 --> 00:34:26,600
I, too, am sorry

320
00:34:27,690 --> 00:34:29,440
for being harsh on you.

321
00:34:31,540 --> 00:34:34,800
- I did it out of...
- Concern?

322
00:34:35,580 --> 00:34:37,040
I get it now.

323
00:34:37,750 --> 00:34:40,159
If I were to go anywhere,

324
00:34:40,590 --> 00:34:42,239
I'd tell you everything.

325
00:34:42,460 --> 00:34:43,460
Okay?

326
00:36:02,070 --> 00:36:03,600
He has fallen asleep.

327
00:36:03,710 --> 00:36:05,090
Please get some rest.

328
00:36:05,120 --> 00:36:07,570
I shall go and fetch some books
from the small manor.

329
00:36:07,600 --> 00:36:10,620
I'll be back. See you in the evening!

330
00:36:15,150 --> 00:36:16,350
I know nothing.

331
00:36:16,390 --> 00:36:17,660
- I did but stumble.
- So do I... I...

332
00:36:17,690 --> 00:36:20,430
- What is all this clutter upon the floor?!
- Sai, why must you push me?

333
00:36:55,280 --> 00:36:58,040
There's got to be something
in that scripture.

334
00:37:05,880 --> 00:37:07,550
What is it that you seek, Master?

335
00:37:07,810 --> 00:37:10,060
As I have mentioned before,
everything has been moved to the main manor.

336
00:37:10,970 --> 00:37:11,970
Chuay.

337
00:37:12,530 --> 00:37:14,130
Have you ever seen me

338
00:37:14,320 --> 00:37:16,440
write something down all by myself?

339
00:37:16,750 --> 00:37:20,280
Like a scripture
that feels very personal,

340
00:37:20,640 --> 00:37:21,640
as if it describes what I've been doing.

341
00:37:22,200 --> 00:37:23,740
Why did you not inquire sooner, Master?

342
00:37:36,280 --> 00:37:37,670
It is this one that you seek.

343
00:37:37,940 --> 00:37:40,270
You used it to steady the wobbly bed.

344
00:37:40,580 --> 00:37:43,320
But it was too thin for its purpose,
so the bed ended up wobbly all the same.

345
00:38:15,260 --> 00:38:16,600
He loved writing notes

346
00:38:16,950 --> 00:38:18,080
like I do, apparently.

347
00:38:26,610 --> 00:38:28,640
Chuay, can you read any of this?

348
00:38:29,340 --> 00:38:33,060
You intentionally wrote it this way
so that it would be illegible to me.

349
00:38:38,940 --> 00:38:42,460
He wrote it in foreign languages
so no one could read it, as I've been doing?

350
00:38:43,810 --> 00:38:45,280
This must be important, then.

351
00:39:13,250 --> 00:39:16,650
It's been a week, but all I can decipher
is "second period."

352
00:39:16,750 --> 00:39:20,280
Chuay says the second period
of the night is from 10 P.M. to 2 A.M.

353
00:39:21,380 --> 00:39:23,440
What would he be doing at 2 A.M.?

354
00:39:25,150 --> 00:39:26,810
Ugh, my head's gonna explode!

355
00:39:26,910 --> 00:39:28,150
Why does an English major

356
00:39:28,180 --> 00:39:30,880
have to tackle history,
ancient Thai, Khom, and Pali scripts?

357
00:39:38,170 --> 00:39:39,120
Klao.

358
00:39:39,740 --> 00:39:41,710
Should you be awake, step outside.

359
00:39:42,020 --> 00:39:44,240
In but two days, Songkran shall arrive,

360
00:39:45,390 --> 00:39:47,440
and our manor
is filled with joyful preparations.

361
00:39:51,750 --> 00:39:52,970
Understood.

362
00:40:07,940 --> 00:40:09,290
Every Songkran,

363
00:40:09,320 --> 00:40:11,130
our relatives, kin,

364
00:40:11,450 --> 00:40:14,320
and elders gather
to pay their respects to my father.

365
00:40:14,800 --> 00:40:17,200
Thus, we must prepare ourselves
for hundreds to arrive.

366
00:40:20,440 --> 00:40:23,040
You, too, have visited us over the years.
Surely you recall, do you not?

367
00:40:31,740 --> 00:40:32,740
Bud.

368
00:40:40,060 --> 00:40:41,560
I see that you have finally joined us.

369
00:40:43,130 --> 00:40:45,080
Everyone is busy with preparations;

370
00:40:45,920 --> 00:40:48,580
I am surprised you did not simply remain in bed
until the next day, Klao.

371
00:40:48,820 --> 00:40:51,830
Oh, Bud, be not so harsh on our boy.

372
00:40:51,860 --> 00:40:53,960
He is still unwell.

373
00:41:01,320 --> 00:41:03,200
You are indeed talented, Master Kaew.

374
00:41:03,470 --> 00:41:05,260
Your flower arrangements are exquisite,

375
00:41:05,290 --> 00:41:07,080
and your cuisine is superb.

376
00:41:18,490 --> 00:41:19,840
Kaew, you're here as well?

377
00:41:40,020 --> 00:41:43,680
From that moment on,
he shunned my presence

378
00:41:45,260 --> 00:41:47,260
and barred me from his manor.

379
00:41:49,080 --> 00:41:51,080
How cruel and heartless.

380
00:41:54,660 --> 00:41:56,430
Doing things for someone you love

381
00:41:57,040 --> 00:41:58,040
is good,

382
00:41:58,670 --> 00:42:01,520
but you also need to love yourself.

383
00:42:25,430 --> 00:42:26,840
With beauty like this,

384
00:42:27,350 --> 00:42:28,920
had this been Phichit,

385
00:42:29,800 --> 00:42:31,480
the whole city would have fallen for you.

386
00:42:38,060 --> 00:42:39,600
If you love yourself

387
00:42:39,790 --> 00:42:41,480
and believe in your qualities,

388
00:42:42,120 --> 00:42:44,760
one day he'll notice them.

389
00:42:45,350 --> 00:42:48,240
But if he doesn't, just forget about him.

390
00:42:50,350 --> 00:42:51,560
I believe that

391
00:42:51,760 --> 00:42:54,730
you'll eventually find
the love you deserve.

392
00:43:23,660 --> 00:43:25,040
Songkran is almost here,

393
00:43:27,250 --> 00:43:29,080
shall we go do something fun?

394
00:43:34,220 --> 00:43:35,230
Phop.

395
00:43:35,900 --> 00:43:37,170
Can you call Chuay for me?

396
00:43:56,540 --> 00:43:58,200
I ask for your blessing.

397
00:44:03,380 --> 00:44:04,760
May you find solace in this land.

398
00:44:04,940 --> 00:44:06,610
- May you live long
- Grant us a blessing.

399
00:44:06,640 --> 00:44:09,040
- and in good health.
- May you prosper.

400
00:44:09,070 --> 00:44:11,220
Whoa, awesome.

401
00:44:11,540 --> 00:44:13,200
This feels like
an Ayutthaya fan meeting event.

402
00:44:17,420 --> 00:44:18,920
There's even a hi-touch and everything.

403
00:44:19,990 --> 00:44:21,160
It really is touching.

404
00:44:22,210 --> 00:44:23,560
Touching all the way up to their foreheads.

405
00:44:24,270 --> 00:44:26,080
May you find solace in this land.

406
00:44:29,470 --> 00:44:30,990
It's really bustling here.

407
00:44:32,500 --> 00:44:37,000
It might not be as lively as the festivals
in Khao San Road or Silom.

408
00:44:39,710 --> 00:44:41,520
People here
don't splash water at each other?

409
00:44:44,600 --> 00:44:46,080
This is Songkran, Klao,

410
00:44:46,110 --> 00:44:48,800
not a wedding.
Why should there be a water pouring ceremony?

411
00:44:50,110 --> 00:44:53,080
Oh, so splashing water at each other
isn't a thing in this era.

412
00:44:53,200 --> 00:44:54,720
So it's just a ceremony, right?

413
00:45:12,030 --> 00:45:15,320
I reckon the crowd will not ease up
until nearly midday, Klao.

414
00:45:15,570 --> 00:45:16,960
Let us pay our respects
at the temple in the meantime.

415
00:45:17,690 --> 00:45:20,440
Sure. Pay respect and make wishes.

416
00:45:21,050 --> 00:45:23,170
Maybe this will make Jom

417
00:45:23,800 --> 00:45:25,040
a bit softer on you.

418
00:45:30,070 --> 00:45:32,680
Come on, Chuay, Sai, and Kong.

419
00:45:32,880 --> 00:45:34,240
Let's pay our respects at the temple.

420
00:45:34,520 --> 00:45:35,720
Master Klao,

421
00:45:35,820 --> 00:45:39,680
may I first go
and powder Lord Phop's face before we proceed?

422
00:45:40,180 --> 00:45:41,560
Sai, what has gotten into you?

423
00:45:41,760 --> 00:45:42,880
Well, this is Songkran.

424
00:45:47,390 --> 00:45:49,320
Making merit to welcome the New Year.

425
00:45:49,360 --> 00:45:51,960
May you weep no more.
May only happiness find you.

426
00:45:53,360 --> 00:45:54,240
Klao.

427
00:45:55,560 --> 00:45:56,560
Master Klao.

428
00:45:57,790 --> 00:45:59,750
- Sai.
- Klao, await me.

429
00:46:02,040 --> 00:46:02,780
Make haste.

430
00:46:09,270 --> 00:46:12,790
May these precious walls of stone

431
00:46:13,150 --> 00:46:15,040
bring you great fortune

432
00:46:15,280 --> 00:46:18,640
and triumph.

433
00:46:19,840 --> 00:46:20,960
- Klao.
- Fortune teller!

434
00:46:22,320 --> 00:46:23,240
Oh?

435
00:46:23,450 --> 00:46:24,960
It is you again, young man.

436
00:46:25,240 --> 00:46:26,780
Today is a fine day,

437
00:46:26,970 --> 00:46:28,320
and I have a gift for you.

438
00:46:28,890 --> 00:46:30,450
Hold out your hand this instant,

439
00:46:30,490 --> 00:46:32,960
for this gift is yours to cherish.

440
00:46:35,220 --> 00:46:37,800
Klao, do you know her?

441
00:46:38,220 --> 00:46:39,840
Rumor has it she is quite mad.

442
00:46:41,750 --> 00:46:43,720
It's okay. She's a kind soul.

443
00:46:44,580 --> 00:46:47,360
A madman meets a deranged soul.

444
00:46:47,490 --> 00:46:49,780
Will they make such a scene again?

445
00:46:53,230 --> 00:46:54,240
Fortune teller...

446
00:46:55,050 --> 00:46:57,240
I dreamed about Klao.

447
00:46:58,850 --> 00:47:02,800
He was actually killed, as you said.

448
00:47:03,400 --> 00:47:06,570
If I can find out who the murderer is,

449
00:47:06,690 --> 00:47:08,080
will I get to return home?

450
00:47:09,260 --> 00:47:10,360
Hold out your hand.

451
00:47:11,860 --> 00:47:13,520
I have something for you.

452
00:47:21,940 --> 00:47:23,760
A new soul dwells within this guise.

453
00:47:24,230 --> 00:47:25,690
A promise has been made.

454
00:47:27,320 --> 00:47:31,060
Fulfill the promise,
restore what was lost, and set wrongs aright.

455
00:47:42,530 --> 00:47:45,320
A star shard from the heavens.

456
00:47:46,320 --> 00:47:48,410
Keep it with you, young man.

457
00:47:48,650 --> 00:47:50,880
Pray with all your heart,

458
00:47:51,090 --> 00:47:54,400
and your prayers shall be answered.

459
00:47:58,120 --> 00:48:00,800
I believe she has completely lost her wits.

460
00:48:00,950 --> 00:48:02,440
Let us leave, Klao.

461
00:48:03,160 --> 00:48:04,680
The crowd is staring at us.

462
00:48:09,210 --> 00:48:10,210
Give me a moment.

463
00:48:10,500 --> 00:48:11,700
I need to talk to her.

464
00:48:12,980 --> 00:48:16,950
Can you say that more simply?

465
00:48:16,980 --> 00:48:18,420
Oracle! Leave at once!

466
00:48:18,450 --> 00:48:20,680
- Cause no trouble within the temple walls!
- It is time I take my leave.

467
00:48:20,940 --> 00:48:22,360
One day, we shall meet again.

468
00:48:22,770 --> 00:48:23,870
Don't go, Fortune teller.

469
00:48:24,760 --> 00:48:26,030
We shall meet again soon.

470
00:48:26,060 --> 00:48:27,360
- Hey!
- This is Songkran, for goodness' sake.

471
00:48:27,390 --> 00:48:28,710
Be gone, you deranged woman!

472
00:48:28,750 --> 00:48:30,080
I shall now depart.

473
00:48:31,060 --> 00:48:32,320
- It is time.
- Hey!

474
00:48:32,490 --> 00:48:34,740
Don't chase her away.
She's not a bad person.

475
00:48:34,780 --> 00:48:37,580
Master Klao, I beg of you,
do not speak with her.

476
00:48:37,680 --> 00:48:38,780
Hey, make haste!

477
00:48:40,530 --> 00:48:41,780
No.

478
00:48:42,080 --> 00:48:43,880
I wasn't done talking to her.

479
00:48:44,120 --> 00:48:45,130
Master Klao.

480
00:48:45,270 --> 00:48:48,200
Should you vanish once more,
Lord Phop would be most distressed.

481
00:49:03,740 --> 00:49:04,840
Klao.

482
00:49:06,130 --> 00:49:08,520
It would seem you care greatly for Oracle.

483
00:49:08,930 --> 00:49:10,080
Do you know her?

484
00:49:11,380 --> 00:49:13,880
Well, I've met her once or twice.

485
00:49:15,490 --> 00:49:17,290
But I...

486
00:49:17,560 --> 00:49:20,080
I don't like it
when she's being judged like that,

487
00:49:22,180 --> 00:49:24,600
the way Klao is the subject of gossip.

488
00:49:25,500 --> 00:49:27,240
Uh, I mean...

489
00:49:27,780 --> 00:49:29,400
Like how I'm the subject of gossip,

490
00:49:30,150 --> 00:49:31,660
being called a drunkard

491
00:49:32,250 --> 00:49:34,620
despite people having no idea
what I've been through.

492
00:49:37,980 --> 00:49:40,800
The same goes for how they gossip about you,

493
00:49:44,630 --> 00:49:45,880
saying you like men

494
00:49:53,960 --> 00:49:55,520
even though they don't know

495
00:49:57,360 --> 00:49:59,520
how painful it is for you.

496
00:50:12,180 --> 00:50:14,440
No one ever truly knows who we are.

497
00:50:15,310 --> 00:50:17,040
All they know is gossip.

498
00:50:23,540 --> 00:50:24,540
Just because...

499
00:50:25,500 --> 00:50:26,870
we're different from others

500
00:50:28,960 --> 00:50:30,570
doesn't mean we're bad.

501
00:50:51,380 --> 00:50:54,240
If Jom had actually understood this

502
00:50:55,960 --> 00:50:58,000
and cared less about what others think,

503
00:51:00,130 --> 00:51:01,790
things would have been easier, right?

504
00:51:29,450 --> 00:51:30,840
Make a wish, Kaew.

505
00:51:33,350 --> 00:51:35,720
This is but a rock.

506
00:51:35,810 --> 00:51:38,120
Such a kind can be found along the river.

507
00:51:40,910 --> 00:51:44,170
Sometimes, ordinary things

508
00:51:44,960 --> 00:51:46,640
may grant you something special.

509
00:51:47,710 --> 00:51:49,770
There's no harm in trying, is there?

510
00:52:26,850 --> 00:52:27,880
May you find solace in this land.

511
00:52:44,540 --> 00:52:45,720
What a relief this is.

512
00:52:46,590 --> 00:52:49,080
With all that racket,

513
00:52:49,650 --> 00:52:51,560
I thought you had run off with Oracle.

514
00:52:53,800 --> 00:52:54,960
A promise

515
00:52:55,290 --> 00:52:57,080
is a promise, is it not?

516
00:52:58,580 --> 00:53:01,560
May I pour scented water over your hands

517
00:53:02,200 --> 00:53:03,680
and receive your blessing?

518
00:53:04,250 --> 00:53:06,470
You asked me that as though
I were one of the older relatives.

519
00:53:07,650 --> 00:53:11,160
Well, you're my brother after all.

520
00:53:15,850 --> 00:53:16,720
Excuse me.

521
00:53:17,160 --> 00:53:19,400
May I jump the queue

522
00:53:19,530 --> 00:53:23,240
and pour scented water over his hands first?

523
00:53:23,710 --> 00:53:24,840
Jump?

524
00:53:26,490 --> 00:53:27,560
Why must he jump?

525
00:53:49,140 --> 00:53:50,350
May you find solace in this land.

526
00:53:51,930 --> 00:53:52,920
Sadhu.

527
00:53:56,840 --> 00:53:57,840
Why wait?

528
00:53:58,500 --> 00:54:00,360
Have you forgotten
how to pour the scented water?

529
00:54:01,050 --> 00:54:02,410
I haven't, of course.

530
00:54:02,640 --> 00:54:04,770
But may I pour it

531
00:54:05,200 --> 00:54:08,320
the Phichit way?

532
00:54:27,720 --> 00:54:29,800
How could you dare treat me so?

533
00:54:36,080 --> 00:54:37,080
You really did it, huh?

534
00:54:37,390 --> 00:54:39,120
How dare you do that to me?

535
00:54:42,650 --> 00:54:43,510
Take that.

536
00:54:45,250 --> 00:54:45,800
Klao!

537
00:54:57,200 --> 00:55:00,990
♫It seems like we are guided by destiny♫

538
00:55:01,020 --> 00:55:04,780
♫It seems like you are the one I used to seek♫

539
00:55:04,820 --> 00:55:08,620
♫Just a second of staring into your eyes♫

540
00:55:08,640 --> 00:55:12,390
♫Feels like we're frozen in time♫

541
00:55:12,430 --> 00:55:19,800
♫Do you know
you make me drift away into fantasy?♫

542
00:55:19,940 --> 00:55:26,700
♫You've captured my heart,
and now it's yours completely♫

543
00:55:26,740 --> 00:55:30,480
♫We'll meet again,
no matter how many lifetimes pass♫

544
00:55:30,500 --> 00:55:34,210
♫It's all yours alone, my beating heart♫

545
00:55:34,270 --> 00:55:38,120
♫May fate guide our paths♫

546
00:55:38,150 --> 00:55:41,450
♫And reunite us through dawns and dusks♫

547
00:55:41,480 --> 00:55:45,500
♫My heart is all yours♫

548
00:55:47,920 --> 00:55:48,960
I bid you farewell.

549
00:55:58,460 --> 00:55:59,680
Jom.

550
00:56:01,600 --> 00:56:03,920
May I have a little fun and do as Klao did?

551
00:56:06,710 --> 00:56:08,540
I must tend to the sick,

552
00:56:09,060 --> 00:56:10,680
so I cannot get wet.

553
00:56:11,230 --> 00:56:12,230
Uh...

554
00:56:12,620 --> 00:56:15,690
In that case, may I pour scented water
over your hands?

555
00:56:15,790 --> 00:56:17,160
Over your feet will do.

556
00:56:18,830 --> 00:56:19,830
Very well.

557
00:56:20,530 --> 00:56:22,680
You may join Klao once you have finished.

558
00:57:56,260 --> 00:57:57,960
- I shall be back.
- Uh...

559
00:58:01,300 --> 00:58:02,300
Jom...

560
00:58:08,420 --> 00:58:09,420
Jom.

561
00:58:10,010 --> 00:58:11,330
Where are you off to?

562
00:58:11,950 --> 00:58:13,840
We must have a proper word first.

563
00:58:14,020 --> 00:58:15,020
Jom.

564
00:58:16,880 --> 00:58:19,000
How much more plainly must I speak?

565
00:58:20,780 --> 00:58:22,270
If you behave so,

566
00:58:23,190 --> 00:58:26,360
people will talk and no longer think
you a gentleman of quality.

567
00:58:29,920 --> 00:58:31,040
I do not care,

568
00:58:31,670 --> 00:58:32,880
so why should you?

569
00:58:34,000 --> 00:58:36,000
If you had no need to care for anyone else,

570
00:58:37,460 --> 00:58:39,580
and if there were no one else in this world,

571
00:58:40,800 --> 00:58:42,320
would you treat me any differently?

572
00:58:43,670 --> 00:58:44,830
I have made myself clear.

573
00:58:46,560 --> 00:58:48,140
I see you only as a brother.

574
00:58:49,080 --> 00:58:50,600
I could never feel otherwise.

575
00:58:52,450 --> 00:58:53,920
Do not trouble me further.

576
00:58:57,200 --> 00:58:58,930
Never once have I felt

577
00:58:59,270 --> 00:59:00,450
any affection for you.

578
00:59:18,640 --> 00:59:20,300
I ought not to have fallen for you.

579
00:59:25,760 --> 00:59:27,800
In the next life,

580
00:59:39,410 --> 00:59:41,920
I hope you will be the one to fall for me.

581
00:59:43,940 --> 00:59:45,550
When that time comes,

582
00:59:47,170 --> 00:59:49,800
I shall not look upon you even once.

583
01:00:46,720 --> 01:00:49,050
All your eccentricities

584
01:00:49,360 --> 01:00:51,080
appear to stem from Phichit.

585
01:00:52,740 --> 01:00:54,920
I am tempted to travel there
this very instant,

586
01:00:55,950 --> 01:00:57,920
if only to discover the truth of it.

587
01:01:08,740 --> 01:01:11,720
Being struck in the head
with that water gun

588
01:01:12,360 --> 01:01:14,140
felt like a sharp blow from a cane.

589
01:01:14,910 --> 01:01:16,810
Truly, it is quite
unsuitable for children's play.

590
01:01:17,720 --> 01:01:19,760
A stray shot to the eye

591
01:01:20,260 --> 01:01:21,880
could cause serious injury.

592
01:01:25,520 --> 01:01:28,900
I'll have Chuay burn all the water guns.

593
01:02:00,040 --> 01:02:01,960
Are you concerned for Kaew and Jom?

594
01:02:05,310 --> 01:02:06,160
Mm.

595
01:02:06,970 --> 01:02:10,560
I'm simply wondering
where they're squabbling now.

596
01:02:15,060 --> 01:02:16,830
If they can bicker, they can make up,

597
01:02:17,850 --> 01:02:19,480
just as we do.

598
01:02:23,400 --> 01:02:25,140
Give Jom some time alone,

599
01:02:25,880 --> 01:02:27,280
and he will feel better.

600
01:03:03,980 --> 01:03:04,980
It is true, Cherd.

601
01:03:05,680 --> 01:03:07,960
Klao has been acting most strangely.

602
01:03:08,200 --> 01:03:09,600
He has ceased his outbursts

603
01:03:09,820 --> 01:03:12,380
and now shares a laugh with Lord Phop,
quite unlike his former self.

604
01:03:14,030 --> 01:03:15,720
It is said that he suffers from amnesia.

605
01:03:16,290 --> 01:03:17,840
The other day,
he visited the House of Pleasure.

606
01:03:18,350 --> 01:03:19,480
I was there.

607
01:03:20,470 --> 01:03:22,080
He could remember neither Sopha

608
01:03:22,360 --> 01:03:23,640
nor the others.

609
01:03:31,660 --> 01:03:33,120
Yet he went there to see Pim,

610
01:03:34,640 --> 01:03:36,640
as though he were trying to vex me.

611
01:03:36,690 --> 01:03:38,060
His amnesia is but a facade.

612
01:03:41,680 --> 01:03:43,320
It is unlikely he would go so far
as to deceive his family.

613
01:03:44,040 --> 01:03:45,720
His taste in food has changed,

614
01:03:46,220 --> 01:03:47,680
and he now resides in the main manor,

615
01:03:48,340 --> 01:03:50,240
which he once refused to do.

616
01:03:53,960 --> 01:03:54,960
Who gave you this information?

617
01:03:56,360 --> 01:03:59,440
Someone at Lord Phop's manor
told me all this.

618
01:04:11,950 --> 01:04:15,160
I truly believe
Master Klao suffers from amnesia.

619
01:04:16,380 --> 01:04:19,440
How could that be possible?

620
01:04:19,590 --> 01:04:23,320
Can amnesia change a man so much?

621
01:04:23,360 --> 01:04:24,970
I think not.

622
01:04:25,000 --> 01:04:26,400
Klao

623
01:04:26,970 --> 01:04:28,040
must have a twin brother.

624
01:04:28,340 --> 01:04:31,720
How could such a thing be possible, Master?

625
01:04:31,880 --> 01:04:34,520
It is, of course, possible.

626
01:04:35,470 --> 01:04:36,680
Listen closely.

627
01:04:37,200 --> 01:04:39,740
Klao disappeared.

628
01:04:39,770 --> 01:04:42,560
His twin has assumed his guise,

629
01:04:42,820 --> 01:04:46,440
posing as Klao to uncover

630
01:04:46,770 --> 01:04:48,840
the one who killed him.

631
01:04:49,870 --> 01:04:51,400
That gave me the creeps.

632
01:04:51,630 --> 01:04:53,040
Master, you are full of it.

633
01:04:53,540 --> 01:04:55,340
I am not.

634
01:04:55,370 --> 01:04:56,770
It is true.

635
01:04:56,800 --> 01:04:59,950
Consider this: if that were truly Klao,

636
01:04:59,980 --> 01:05:01,850
would he not remember everything?

637
01:05:01,880 --> 01:05:06,330
He once overturned the tables
and threw a terrible tantrum.

638
01:05:06,360 --> 01:05:08,230
He must also remember that

639
01:05:08,260 --> 01:05:11,720
it was I who cast him out.

640
01:05:11,750 --> 01:05:16,020
Then he ought to resent me
and report me to Lord Phop.

641
01:05:16,050 --> 01:05:19,680
Once he was informed,
he came to the teahouse and gave me a beating.

642
01:05:19,960 --> 01:05:20,760
But where?

643
01:05:21,550 --> 01:05:24,600
Where is he?
He has yet to give me a beating.

644
01:05:24,890 --> 01:05:29,350
I remember that 28 chairs had been replaced.

645
01:05:29,390 --> 01:05:32,860
I counted them all and noticed that
two had broken legs.

646
01:05:32,890 --> 01:05:36,920
As for the vase, this is the twentieth one.

647
01:05:36,950 --> 01:05:40,900
He even punched a hole clean
through the ceiling...

648
01:05:59,530 --> 01:06:01,760
Why is it so quiet tonight?

649
01:06:02,160 --> 01:06:03,240
Where's everyone?

650
01:06:03,650 --> 01:06:04,800
Today is the New Year.

651
01:06:05,770 --> 01:06:07,600
People are gathering
at the temple for the festival.

652
01:06:08,830 --> 01:06:10,430
Kindly join me tomorrow.

653
01:06:10,980 --> 01:06:12,880
The festivities last
for three days and three nights.

654
01:06:13,300 --> 01:06:14,380
You promise?

655
01:06:14,990 --> 01:06:18,000
If you're on duty,
you need to find a way to swap shifts.

656
01:06:34,470 --> 01:06:35,630
I promise.

657
01:06:37,030 --> 01:06:38,340
Now, rest.

658
01:06:38,790 --> 01:06:40,360
You have been a little rascal all day.

659
01:06:44,060 --> 01:06:45,280
Good night, and sweet dreams.

660
01:06:47,130 --> 01:06:48,170
Sweet dreams.

661
01:06:52,580 --> 01:06:53,760
No, no dreams.

662
01:06:55,310 --> 01:06:56,600
It will let us sleep soundly

663
01:06:57,430 --> 01:06:58,840
and get a good rest.

664
01:07:02,190 --> 01:07:03,440
Goodnight and no dreams,

665
01:07:04,350 --> 01:07:05,200
you.

666
01:07:51,600 --> 01:07:52,610
Klao!

667
01:07:53,580 --> 01:07:54,730
Where in the world are you hiding?!

668
01:08:15,580 --> 01:08:17,240
Whither do you think to escape me!

669
01:08:36,000 --> 01:08:37,260
- What is the matter?!
- I had a nightmare.

670
01:08:46,970 --> 01:08:48,069
What was your nightmare about?

671
01:08:49,560 --> 01:08:51,240
You can tell me anything.

672
01:08:55,819 --> 01:08:56,930
I can't.

673
01:08:58,450 --> 01:08:59,640
How am I supposed to tell you

674
01:09:00,550 --> 01:09:01,920
that Klao, the one you love,

675
01:09:02,979 --> 01:09:04,470
has already been murdered?

676
01:09:10,550 --> 01:09:11,550
Never mind it.

677
01:09:13,050 --> 01:09:14,620
Tell me whenever you feel ready.

678
01:09:26,850 --> 01:09:28,080
Tonight,

679
01:09:28,840 --> 01:09:30,200
might you share my bed?

680
01:10:12,920 --> 01:10:17,500
I simply wonder
how people go about courting another.

681
01:10:18,410 --> 01:10:21,240
Klao, the one from our childhood, Phop?

682
01:10:21,750 --> 01:10:23,000
Is it that odd?

683
01:10:23,140 --> 01:10:25,180
Are you not the same, or am I mistaken?

684
01:10:25,720 --> 01:10:28,510
The servants said
you have yet to eat anything all day.

685
01:10:29,000 --> 01:10:30,640
I have brought you some of your favorites.

686
01:10:31,040 --> 01:10:32,240
It is simply impossible.

687
01:10:32,440 --> 01:10:33,640
Then so be it.

688
01:10:33,860 --> 01:10:35,440
Pray tell me, my good Physician,

689
01:10:36,350 --> 01:10:38,050
what ought I to do?

690
01:10:38,860 --> 01:10:42,080
Are you... more worried about me

691
01:10:42,900 --> 01:10:43,680
or

692
01:10:45,200 --> 01:10:46,840
Klao, the one you knew?

693
01:10:48,280 --> 01:10:50,170
I believe you know in your heart
well enough

694
01:10:50,470 --> 01:10:52,090
how I feel about you.

695
01:10:52,120 --> 01:10:55,630
♫Only you I want to see,
no matter how many lifetimes pass♫

696
01:10:55,660 --> 01:10:59,430
♫It's all yours to keep, this beating heart♫

697
01:10:59,460 --> 01:11:03,280
♫I'll plead to the stars so that we'll meet again♫

698
01:11:03,310 --> 01:11:07,060
♫I wish to fall in love with you
until the very end♫

699
01:11:07,100 --> 01:11:10,890
♫We'll meet again,
no matter how many lifetimes pass♫

700
01:11:10,940 --> 01:11:14,630
♫It's all yours alone, my beating heart♫

701
01:11:14,660 --> 01:11:18,560
♫May fate guide our paths♫

702
01:11:18,590 --> 01:11:21,950
♫And reunite us through dawns and dusks♫

703
01:11:21,980 --> 01:11:29,360
♫My heart is all yours♫

704
01:11:37,620 --> 01:11:44,710
♫Only you I want to see,
no matter how many lifetimes pass♫

705
01:11:47,520 --> 01:11:51,640
[Love Upon a Time Series]
